olive oil
3 potato
40 g plant-based butter
2 tbs plant-based milk
2 clove garlic
1 carrot
1 leek
1 tomato
1 packet plant-based mince
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet tomato paste
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 tsp brown sugar
½ cup water
1 sachet sesame seeds
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)

• Preheat grill to high. Boil the kettle. Half-fill a large saucepan with boiling water, then add a generous pinch of salt.
• Peel potato and cut into large chunks.
• Cook potato in the boiling water, over high heat, until easily pierced with a fork, 12-15 minutes. Drain and return to the pan.
• Add the plant-based butter and plant-based milk to the potato and season with salt. Mash until smooth.

TIP: Save time and get more fibre by leaving the potato unpeeled.

• Meanwhile, finely chop garlic and carrot. Thinly slice leek. Roughly chop tomato.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook plant-based mince, carrot and leek, stirring, until softened, 6-7 minutes.
• Add garlic, garlic & herb seasoning and tomato paste, and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium, then add vegetable stock powder, the brown sugar and water, and simmer until slightly thickened, 2-3 minutes. Season with pepper.

• Transfer veggie mince filling to a baking dish. Spread evenly with potato mash.
• Sprinkle over sesame seeds and drizzle with olive oil.
• Grill pie until golden, 8-10 minutes.

• Meanwhile, combine tomato, mixed salad leaves and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil in a large bowl. Season to taste.

• Divide classic veggie mince potato topped pie between plates.
• Serve with tomato salad. Enjoy!